(2446, 863, 'wpcf-resume_field', '2009- present – Patent Attorney with Ehrilch and Fenster\r\n\r\n2007-2009 – Patent Attorney with Eitan Mehulel Law Gffice in Herzliya, Il.\r\n\r\n1979-2007 – Partner in New York City Patent and General Practice law firms handling IP matters and trials of Products Liability matters for manufacturers and insurance companies\r\n\r\n1973-1979 – Assistant General Counsel of Manufacturer of circuit breakers and other electrical power distribution equipment handling patent matters contracts and defense of product liability claims\r\n\r\n1965-1973 – Associate and Partner in Washington, D.C. Patent Law Firm\r\n\r\n1962-1965 – Patent Examiner, U.S. Patent and Trademark Office specializing in electronic switching systems, computer controlled telemetering systems and computer memory systems.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(2447, 863, 'wpcf-experience_field', 'Following several years as an Examiner in the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office and 42 years as a patent attorney, and as a trial lawyer specializing in Intellectual Property litigation and defense of manufactures and insurance companies in products liability matters, Mr. Hoffman moved to Israel and at the beginning of 2009, joined Dr. Ehrlich’s firm.\r\n\r\nHe now prepares and prosecutes patent applications world-wide, especially in the field of medical products, counsels clients in a full range of IP issues, and provides litigation support, especially for IP litigation in the U.S.\r\n\r\nHis experience covers the full range of IP issues, including general counseling on patent and trademark matters; preparation and prosecution of patent and trademark applications for domestic and foreign clients; preparation of validity, freedom to operate, and infringement opinions; negotiation and preparation of IP licensing agreements; conducting Contested Proceedings (Interferences, Reexaminations, Trademark Oppositions) in USPTO; and patent and trademark litigation in U.S. and Europe.\r\n\r\nHis experience in the field of products liability includes conducting trials and appeals of product liability cases for manufactures and insurers; and client counseling on product safety, product liability prevention, and product recall planning.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(2448, 863, 'wpcf-education_field', '1962-1965 – J.D. degree from George Washington University School of Law, Washington, D.C.\r\n\r\n1958-1962 - B.S. in Electrical Engineering degree from Massachusetts Institute of Technology, Cambridge MA\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(2449, 863, 'wpcf-academic_awards', '1965 – Order of the Coif (U.S. National Law School Honor Society)'),
(2450, 863, 'wpcf-voluntary_activities', '1985-1995 – Member and Chairman, U.S. Delegation to Technical Committee 56 of international Electrotechnical Commission on Reliability\r\n\r\n1858-1999 – Member, American Society for Quality Control\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(2451, 863, 'wpcf-admissions', '1965 – Registered to Practice before U.S. Patent and Trademark Office\r\n\r\n1966 – District of Columbia Local and Federal Courts\r\n\r\n1969 – Maryland State Courts\r\n\r\n1975 – U.S. Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit\r\n\r\n1979 – New York State and Federal Courts)\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
