(2502, 868, 'wpcf-resume_field', '2001-2006 Affiliated with Ehrlich &amp; Partners involved in the drafting and prosecution of patent applications\r\n\r\n2006 Affiliated with Ehrlich &amp; Fenster\r\n\r\n1998-2004 and 2008-2011 Chief Scientist and later CEO of 3ality Inc., designer of glasses-free 3D screens\r\n\r\n1998-2001 Chief Scientist of Tsunami Inc., then designer of internet based information retrieval systems\r\n\r\n1998-2001 Chief Scientist of Hard Software Ltd, designer of handwriting recognition systems based in image analysis and using a proprietary information retrieval system\r\n\r\nEarlier: Inventor and Designer of the IZE software, a prize-winning information retrieval system\r\n\r\nEarlier still: ‘Computer Person’ for בית ספר למינהל עסקים and Library and Archive School of the University of Jerusalem, and\r\n\r\nA really long time ago: real-time programmer for the U.S. Navy\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(2503, 868, 'wpcf-experience_field', 'Mr. Kleinberger is largely an autodidact, a fact reflected in various aspects of his career. He served as a supervisor of field psychologists in the Israel Defense Forces Field Psychology unit, despite not holding a formal degree in Psychology. He taught computer science in the School of Library Science of the Hebrew University before engaging in the formal study of Computer Science.\r\n\r\nMr. Kleinberger studied philosophy, creative writing, and therapeutic and organizational psychology. He holds several U.S. patents in computer science (hypertext technology, information retrieval), and several patents (recently sold) in stereoscopic three-dimensional displays, which are electronically driven optical systems\r\n\r\nSeveral of Mr. Kleinberger’s inventions have been implemented. One was reported by Time Magazine and recognized as “Best New Application of the Year” by the American Software Publishers’ Association\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(2504, 868, 'wpcf-education_field', '1965 B.A. degree in Philosophy from Yale University, USA\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n1967 MFA Awarded by the University of Iowa, USA\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n1973-1977 Formal and informal training in therapeutic and organizational psychology\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n1982 Received Diploma as Systems Analyst from the AML Institute, Israel\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(2505, 868, 'wpcf-academic_awards', 'Yale degree was awarded Cum Laude with departmental “High Honors”, after 3 years of study instead of the usual four.'),
(2506, 868, 'wpcf-rankings_recognitions', 'The IZE system, invented and co-designed by Mr. Kleinberger, won Best New Application of Year” by the American Software Publishers’ association and Editors Choice in PC Magazine'),
(2507, 868, 'wpcf-degrees', 'Technical Advisor'),
