(2920, 313, 'wpcf-resume_field', 'Since 2004 , Dr. Revital Green serves as the manager of the Chemistry and Pharma department at Ehrlich &amp;Fenster.\r\n\r\nAffiliated with Ehrlich &amp; Partners since October 2000, drafting and prosecuting patent applications in a variety of fields including Biotech, Agrotech, Medicine, Pharmaceuticals, Chemistry and Medical Devices.\r\n\r\n1992 Employed as a researcher at Ramot, Tel-Aviv University, Israel'),
(2921, 313, 'wpcf-experience_field', 'Revital Green is the manager of the Chemistry and Pharmacology Department in Ehrlich &amp;Fenster.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDr. Green has a B. Sc. in Chemistry, a M. Sc. in Chemistry and Biothechnology and a Ph. D. in Chemistry.\r\n\r\nThe Chemistry and Pharmacology Department in Ehrlich &amp; Fenster, headed by Dr. Green, handles IP matters of dozens clients, including leading universities and academic institutions in Israel, as well as well-known pharmaceutical companies, start-ups and private clientele, and is involved in drafting and prosecuting patent applications, including opposition procedures, rendering opinions, in IP wise Due Diligence processes, and in devising IP and commercialization strategies.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(2922, 313, 'wpcf-education_field', '1994-1998 Ph.D. degree in Organic Chemistry from the Tel-Aviv University, Israel\r\n\r\nEmployed as an instructor at the Organic Chemistry Students’ Laboratory, Tel-Aviv University, Israel\r\n\r\n1990-1993 M.Sc. degree (with distinction) in Organic Chemistry (Major) and Biotechnology (Minor) from the Tel-Aviv University, Israel\r\n\r\n1986-1989 B.Sc. degree in Chemistry from the Tel-Aviv University, Israel\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
