(2985, 291, 'wpcf-experience_field', 'Amit is an honors graduate of the Academic College of Law in Ramat-Gan, and maintains a varied civil practice covering a variety of legal domains. His affiliation with Ehrlich &amp; Partners (currently Ehrlich &amp; Fenster) began in 2002. Amit serves as the firm’s chief Legal Counsel.\r\n\r\nAmit Ehrlich is a field-proven attorney with extensive experience in commercial litigation as well as in Intellectual Property, corporate, commercial and banking law.\r\n\r\nAmit focus on assisting patent holders to monetize their patents, including developing and implementing licensing programs and conducting patent sales negotiations for clients ranging from individual inventors to large corporations and founded IPtrade - www.iptrade.com , an Ehrlich initiative for patent monetization where Amit serves as the CEO.'),
(2986, 291, 'wpcf-education_field', '1995-1999 LL.B. degree (Honors) from the Academic College of Law in Ramat-Gan, Israel.'),
(2987, 291, 'wpcf-rankings_recognitions', 'The IAM magazine 2013 has chosen Adv. Amit Ehrlich to be one of the 300 Worlds Leading IP Strategists for the second successive year.'),
