(2993, 873, 'wpcf-resume_field', '2004- Present Patent Attorney, Ehrlich &amp; Fenster\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">• Consulted on transactional legal matters, including contracts, licensing, ownership, and technology transfer issues.</span>\r\n\r\n• Drafted dozens of patent applications in a wide variety of technical fields.\r\n\r\n• Prosecuted patent applications before a number of patent offices including Europe, Japan, Canada, China, Eurasia (Russia and the former Soviet Republics) and the USPTO in PCT and national applications, including patent appeals and oppositions.\r\n\r\n• Provided freedom to operate, patentability and invalidity analyses.\r\n\r\n• Assumed responsibility for management of numerous client patent portfolios.\r\n\r\n• Served as primary client contact at the firm for multiple clients.\r\n\r\n• Supervised foreign associates in litigation and patent matters in multiple jurisdictions.\r\n\r\n1999-2004 Intellectual Property Attorney\r\n\r\n• Filed and prosecuted scores of domestic trademark applications.\r\n\r\n• Managed foreign associates and prosecution of Patent Cooperation Treaty and international trademark cases.\r\n\r\n• Maintained client domestic and international trademark portfolios and formulated strategies with the clients for maximizing exposure and usage of their trademarks.\r\n\r\n• Handled transactional legal matters, including contracts, licensing and ownership issues.\r\n\r\n• Drafted and prosecuted patent applications, including telecommunications, biomedical, business method, electrical, and mechanical technologies.\r\n\r\n• Performed patentability, infringement and invalidity analyses.\r\n\r\n• Litigation experience, including pleadings, motion practice, discovery and settlement negotiations in various intellectual property matters, experienced in Trademark Trial and Appeals Board cases in the USPTO.\r\n\r\n1997-1998 Summer Associate\r\n\r\n• Assisted with the preparation of patent applications and Office Action responses.\r\n\r\n• Filed and prosecuted numerous trademark applications.\r\n\r\n• Prepared pleadings and discovery in domestic and international patent infringement cases.\r\n\r\n• Worked closely with supervising attorney on multiple trademark infringement litigation matters.\r\n\r\n• Responsible for proposing a damages argument that resulted in a seven-figure judgment for the client.\r\n\r\n1995  Research Technician, Dept. of Developmental Biology and Anatomy,  University of South Carolina, School of Medicine\r\n\r\n• Assisted in preparation of experiments for Space Shuttle flight.\r\n\r\n• Conceived, designed and performed laboratory experiments for research Ph.D.s in the field of tissue engineering of the myocardium.\r\n\r\n• Produced reports of findings for faculty.'),
