(3129, 795, 'wpcf-resume_field', '2008-2012: Director, Software, Marketing and Technology at Techtium LTD (Tel Aviv, Israel), a company producing power management ASICs.\r\n\r\n2001 to 2008: Co-founder and CTO at MicroMRI Inc. (Philadelphia, PA, USA), a company founded by Dr. Gomberg to commercialize the MRI-based Virtual Bone Biopsy. This technology, developed at the University of Pennsylvania, allows assessment of bone quality from MRI scanners by converting their capabilities from millimeter scale images to micrometer scale images and performing advanced image processing methods.\r\n\r\n2003 to 2008: Lecturer – academic appointment Radiology, Hadassah Medical Organization (Jerusalem, Israel) where Dr. Gomberg implemented cutting edge research technologies as clinical protocols.\r\n\r\n1985 to 1995: Scientific and Data Acquisition Programmer at University of California San Francisco (CA, USA), Lead Control LTD (Tel Aviv, Israel), ORLEV Scientific Computing LTD, (Yavne, Israel), I.R.T. LTD (Tel-Aviv, Israel), and Ben-Gurion University (Beer-Sheva, Israel).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3130, 795, 'wpcf-experience_field', 'Dr. Gomberg has joined Erlich and Fenster as a technical advisor in 2013.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Erlich and Fenster, Dr. Gomberg has published 20 articles in peer-reviewed journals and over 35 abstracts at international conferences. He has given over 15 lectures at international conferences, workshops and major universities. As part of his doctoral dissertation Dr. Gomberg has published four granted patents (US Patents 6975894, 7477770, 7643664, and 7769214) and participated in multiple freedom to operate searches, prior art searches, and evaluation of potential technologies for licensing.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3131, 795, 'wpcf-education_field', '2003 Postdoctoral Fellowship in Endocrinology at the Hospital of the University of Pennsylvania\r\n\r\n1996-2002 Ph.D. in Bioengineering from the University of Pennsylvania\r\n\r\n1995-1996 M.S.E. in Bioengineering from the University of Pennsylvania\r\n\r\n1987-1990 B.Sc. cum laude in Material Engineering from the Ben-Gurion University\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3132, 795, 'wpcf-academic_awards', 'Dr. Gomberg was honored with the following awards:\r\n\r\n1988 – BGU Rector’s Award, Israeli Knesset Scholastic Excellence Award\r\n\r\n1989 – BGU Dean’s Award, Victor Ram Academic Achievement Award\r\n\r\n1990 – BGU Dean’s Award\r\n\r\n2002 – Wharton Business Plan Competition winner; University of Pennsylvania\r\n\r\n2003 – Southwest Business Plan Competition winner; Rice University\r\n\r\n2004 – Academic Business Plan Competition winner; University of San Francisco\r\n\r\n2004 – American Society of Aging “Baby Boomer” business plan competition winner\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
