(3257, 814, 'wpcf-experience_field', 'Graduating in 1966 with an Engineering Degree, Sol began working as a Patent Examiner in the U.S. Patent &amp; Trademark Office while studying Law in the evenings. Having obtaining his law degree, Sol worked as a Patent Attorney for the Department of the Navy, and subsequently headed up their Patent Attorney Training program. After a stint as a patent attorney with NASA, Sol returned to the Navy and headed up several Navy offices, including their premiere facility at the Naval Research Laboratory. In 1997, Sol came to Israel, and worked as a patent attorney at the patent firm that Gal Ehrlich worked, and joined Gal Ehrlich''s firm at the time of its inception.'),
