(3287, 301, 'wpcf-resume_field', 'In 1997, Mr. Fenster co-founded the firm of Fenster &amp; Company, later to merge in 2006 with the practice of Ehrlich &amp; Partners, becoming Ehrlich &amp; Fenster, Israel’s largest &amp; leading Patent Attorneys firm.\r\n\r\n1994 Mr. Fenster joined the practice of Sanford T. Colb &amp; Co. as a Patent Attorney trainee.'),
(3288, 301, 'wpcf-experience_field', 'Mr. Maier Fenster leads the activity of Ehrlich &amp; Fenster’s Medical Devices department, which focuses on drafting and prosecuting Bioengineering, Medical Devices and Medical Imaging patent applications. Mr. Fenster specializes in groundbreaking and interdisciplinary inventions, as well as in helping build IP portfolios that add value to companies, especially start-up companies in the fields of Image Processing, Physics, Electronic Systems, Computer Science, Internet and Bioinformatics.\r\n\r\nMr. Fenster was involved in drafting and prosecution of thousands of patent applications and in oppositions and litigation support worldwide. He was also involved in drafting patentability opinions, freedom to operate opinions and infringement opinions.\r\n\r\nMr. Fenster is an inventor in about 30 patent applications in the fields of software and medical devices (mechanics and electronics).\r\n\r\nMr. Fenster lectures in academic and professional forums and was a mentor in Talpiyot courses and involved in the selection of students for the Talpiyot Program.'),
(3289, 301, 'wpcf-education_field', '1989 B.Sc. (Honors) degree in Mathematics &amp; Physics from the Hebrew University of Jerusalem (Talpiyot Program), Israel\r\n\r\n1994 M.Sc. degree in Computer Science from Bar-Ilan University, Ramat-Gan, Israel\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3290, 301, 'wpcf-admissions', '1996 Mr. Fenster was licensed to practice before the Israel Patent Office as a Patent Attorney and as a Patent Agent at the US Patent &amp; Trademark Office.'),
(3291, 301, 'wpcf-degrees', 'Head of Medical Devices Department'),
(3292, 640, 'wpcf-main-team', 'biotech'),
(3293, 640, 'wpcf-email', 'hadassa'),
(3294, 640, 'wpcf-resume_field', '2001 Affiliated with Ehrlich &amp; Partners.'),
(3295, 640, 'wpcf-experience_field', 'Since 2001 Dr. Waterman has been involved in the preparation and prosecution of patent applications. Since 2004 managing the biotech department in Ehrlich &amp; Fenster. To date, the department is made up of 7 patent attorneys, all of which have a PhD in different disciplines of biology.\r\n\r\nDr. Waterman specializes in IP matters in fields such as cell biology, bio-informatics, immunology, biochemistry, nanotechnology, medical devices, agrotech and nutrition.\r\n\r\nDr. Waterman is involved in drafting and prosecuting patent applications, including opposition procedures, in rendering opinions regarding IP matters, in IP Due Diligence processes, and in devising IP and commercialization strategies.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe Biotech department managed by Dr. Waterman has won the Corporate INTL Global Award 2012 as the “Biotechnology Law Firm of the Year in Israel”.\r\n\r\nDr. Waterman has won the “Biotech Patent Attorney of the 2014 Year in Israel” by GlobalLawExperts.'),
(3296, 640, 'wpcf-education_field', '1994-2000 Ph.D. degree in Molecular Biology from the Weizmann Institute of Science, Israel.\r\n\r\n1991-1993 B.Sc. degree in Biology from the Hebrew University of Jerusalem, Israel.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDuring her academic career, Dr. Waterman authored over 15 papers and reviews in the fields of Cell Biology, Biochemistry and Molecular Biology.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3297, 640, 'wpcf-academic_awards', '1996-1998 Dr. Waterman was honored with the Gabriela Goldschleger honorary scholarship.'),
(3298, 640, 'wpcf-rankings_recognitions', 'The Biotech department managed by Dr. Waterman has won the Corporate INTL Global Award 2012 as the “Biotechnology Law, Firm of the Year in Israel”.'),
(3299, 640, 'wpcf-admissions', '2003 Licensed as a Patent Attorney before the Israel Patent &amp; Trademark Office.'),
(3300, 640, 'wpcf-degrees', 'Head of Biotech Department'),
(3301, 788, 'wpcf-main-team', 'hi-tech'),
(3302, 788, 'wpcf-email', 'geoff'),
(3303, 788, 'wpcf-practice-areas', 'Patents\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3304, 788, 'wpcf-resume_field', '2000 – present: Patent Attorney with Ehrlich and Partners, later Ehrlich and Fenster, establishing the firm’s Hi-Tech department.\r\n\r\n1997 – 2000: Patent Attorney with Sanford T Colb, Israel. Qualified as an Israel Patent Attorney\r\n\r\n1997 – Present: Fellow of the UK Chartered Institute of Patent Attorneys (CIPA)\r\n\r\n1990 – 1997: Patent Attorney with Haseltine Lake, UK, qualified as a UK chartered Patent Agent and European Patent Attorney.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3305, 788, 'wpcf-experience_field', 'Geoff Melnick began in the IP field in 1990 in the UK with Haseltine Lake, one of the country’s most prestigious IP firms, handling an International client list that included such multi-national companies as Fujitsu, Sharp and Siemens.\r\n\r\nHe moved to Israel in 1997 and joined Dr Gal Ehrlich at the establishment of his firm in 2000.\r\n\r\nSince then Geoff has been involved with an exciting mixture of mature companies and big and small startups, seeing many of the startups from their first patent application through investment rounds to successful multi-million dollar exits.\r\n\r\nGeoff has been involved in the preparation of patent applications in Hardware, Software, Communications, Physics, and Medical Devices, in particular RF engineering, microwave antennae, satellite communications, sound and image processing, data compression, pattern recognition, control and measurement engineering, computer modeling, communications protocols, cellular and roaming infrastructures, ultrasound, firewalls, cryptography, semiconductors, computer architecture, memories, computer input devices and interfaces, smart cards, semiconductor lasers, fiber optics, CNC devices and robotics, seismic imaging and electrical machines.\r\n\r\nHe has also been involved in due diligence assessments, opposition and appeal proceedings before the European Patent Office and litigation support, as well as providing strategy and portfolio management advice, and has also conducted numerous hearings at the USPTO.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3306, 788, 'wpcf-education_field', '1991-2 Certificate of Intellectual Property Law, Queen Mary College, University of London UK.\r\n\r\n1986 – 1990 BEng. (Hons) degree in electrical and electronic engineering from the University of Manchester, UK\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3307, 788, 'wpcf-voluntary_activities', 'Runs, swims and works out on a regular basis\r\n\r\nA keen follower of the latest developments in science and technology, as well as studying philosophy, history, Talmud and Kaballah.\r\n\r\nWrites his own computer programs, mainly in Delphi Pascal.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHas stood in elections for public office both in the UK and in Israel\r\n\r\nHas been a long-time supporter of Kulanu, an organization that works around the world to locate and support isolated and emerging Jewish communities and help them to reconnect to the wider Jewish world\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3308, 788, 'wpcf-admissions', 'Geoff Melnick has been a registered UK Patent Attorney since 1997, a registered Israel Patent attorney since 1999 and has been qualified to practice before the European Patent Office since 1997.'),
(3309, 788, 'wpcf-degrees', 'Head of Hi-Tech Department'),
(3319, 777, 'wpcf-main-team', 'trademarks'),
(3320, 777, 'wpcf-email', 'yoel'),
(3321, 777, 'wpcf-practice-areas', 'Trademarks\r\n\r\nDesign'),
(3322, 777, 'wpcf-resume_field', '2003- Affiliated with Ehrlich &amp; Partners.\r\n\r\n2001-2002 Internship at the office of Dr. Zvi Tamir &amp; Co. Law Offices, specialized in International and Intellectual Property Law.\r\n\r\n2000-2001 VocalTec Communications Ltd. - Legal Assistant in the IP Department.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3323, 777, 'wpcf-experience_field', 'Adv. Yoel Szybel is the head of the Trademark Group of Ehrlich &amp; Fenster.\r\n\r\nAdv. Sztybel practices in all aspects of Intellectual Property Law, concentrating mainly on domestic and foreign trademark prosecution, as well as trademark clearance and enforcement. Adv. Sztybel has gained many years of experience in representing clients in opposition and cancellation proceedings before the Israeli Patent &amp; Trademark Office.\r\n\r\nAdv. Sztybel has worked on trademark matters around the world, prosecuting foreign trademark applications, including International Registrations filed through WIPO, customs seizures, cease and desist letters, settlement agreements.\r\n\r\nAdv. Sztybel also manages the Design department of Ehrlich &amp; Fenster and counsels clients on the optimum IP strategy offering them a full spectrum of protection for their products and inventions. Mr. Sztybel has experience in all stages of the design patent prosecution process before the USPTO and other foreign jurisdictions.\r\n\r\nAdv. Sztybel represents clients across a range of industries, including hi-tech companies, medical devices, biotech and agrotech, pharmaceutical, luxury goods, jewelry, food and beverages and personal care products.\r\n\r\nOutside Israel, Adv. Sztybel has also assisted in copyright and trademark litigations. He has also experience in UDRP proceedings, and prepared and filed copyright applications before the US Copyright Office.'),
(3324, 777, 'wpcf-education_field', '1997-2001 LL.B. degree from Bar-Ilan University, Israel'),
(3325, 777, 'wpcf-admissions', '2003 - Admitted to practice, Israel Bar.\r\n\r\nMember of INTA, and ECTA organizations.'),
(3326, 777, 'wpcf-degrees', 'Head of Trademark Department'),
