(3514, 531, 'wpcf-resume_field', '2005 Affiliated with Ehrlich &amp; Partners as a Technical Advisor.\r\n\r\n2004-2005 Gilat, Bareket &amp; Co. Attorneys at Law – Articled Clerk, engaged in patent litigation. Was directly involved in several biotechnology and pharmaceutical patent disputes. Assisted in litigation of trademarks, copyrights and trade-secrets cases before the Patents, Trademarks and Design Registrar and in various courts in Israel.\r\n\r\n2004 IViR – Institute for Information of the Faculty of law of the University of Amsterdam. Engaged as a research assistant in several projects and conferences regarding Copyright and Media Law.\r\n\r\n2002-2004 Rafael-Armament Development Authority – Worked as a software programmer on a number of image processing and real time projects.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3515, 531, 'wpcf-experience_field', 'Adv. Roy Melzer manages the activity of Ehrlich &amp; Fenster Software and Information System department, which focuses on drafting and prosecuting patent applications for various computer based inventions including security (cyber), database management, advertisement systems, image processing based inventions such as image compression (decoders and protocols), medical imaging and real time image processing inventions, parallel processing, telecommunications and Internet related patent applications for International and Israeli companies and entrepreneurs.\r\n\r\nRoy specializes in cases involving complex technical subject matter and legal issues, especially those relating to computer implemented inventions. Roy also gained extensive experience in prosecution matters concerning imaging, hardware, optics, and technical implementations of business processes.\r\n\r\nHe is also substantially experienced in the process of developing IP portfolio for startups and in providing due diligence reports and freedom to operate opinions.\r\n\r\nAdv. Melzer was noted for his expertise in patent matters in the 2011 and 2012 editions of Managing Intellectual Property Handbook.\r\n\r\nAdv. Roy Melzer manages drafting and prosecuting priority patent applications for clients such as IBM, Samsung, CyberArk, Top Image Systems, Medical Sensible and many others.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3516, 531, 'wpcf-education_field', '2000-2004 LL.B. Law degree, Faculty of Law, Haifa University, Israel\r\n\r\n2000-2004 B.Sc. degree in Computer Science from Haifa University, Israel\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3517, 531, 'wpcf-rankings_recognitions', 'Adv. Melzer was noted for his expertise in patent matters in the 2011 and 2012 editions of Managing Intellectual Property Handbook.'),
(3518, 531, 'wpcf-admissions', '2006 Licensed as a Patent Attorney before the Israel Patent &amp; Trademark Office.\r\n\r\n2006 Admitted to practice, Israel Bar.\r\n\r\nMember of INTA, AIPPI, and PTMG organizations\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
