(3543, 843, 'wpcf-resume_field', '2012 Affiliated with Ehrlich &amp; Fenster as a Technical Advisor, involved in the drafting and prosecuting patent applications in a variety of fields including Biotech, Agrotech, Medicine, Pharmaceuticals, Chemistry and Medical Devices\r\n\r\n2011-2012 Scientific Writer at PolyDNA, Inc., Israel, writing and editing scientific articles and features for business, trade and professional publications relating to viral infection treatments\r\n\r\n2007-2011 Teaching Instructor in a General Chemistry Course, Bar-Ilan University, Israel\r\n\r\n2006-2007 Teaching Instructor at the Materials Science Students’ Laboratory, Bar-Ilan University, Israel\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3544, 843, 'wpcf-education_field', '2009-2011 MBA (Finance) degree from the Bar-Ilan University, Israel\r\n\r\n2007-2011 Ph.D. degree in Chemistry of Materials from the Bar-Ilan University, Israel\r\n\r\n2005-2007 M.Sc. degree (cum laude) in Chemistry from the Bar-Ilan University, Israel\r\n\r\n1999-2004 B.Sc. degree (cum laude) in Life Sciences and Chemistry from the Open University, Israel\r\n\r\nDuring his academic career, Dr. Applerot authored over 15 papers and chapters in books in the interdisciplinary field of nanotechnology and microbiology\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
(3545, 843, 'wpcf-academic_awards', 'Dr. Applerot was honored with the following academic awards:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n2009-2011 - The Bar-Ilan Center for Nanotechnology award.\r\n\r\n2007-2011- Bar-Ilan President’s Excellence award.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
