(700, 2, '2008-03-01 12:00:08', '2008-03-01 12:00:08', 'The Managing IP World Survey found Ehrlich &amp; Fenster\r\nto be Israel’s No. 1 Patent Attorneys firm. The Managing IP ranking is based on extensive research\r\nand interviews with patent practitioners worldwide. A team of researchers based in London, Hong\r\nKong and New York contacted firms in 65 jurisdictions to ask them for information and feedback on\r\nthe rankings.\r\n\r\nThe results of the survey highlight the unparallel level of service offered to clients by the\r\nEhrlich &amp; Fenster team. Managing IP surveys concentrate on quality of services offered to clients\r\nand associates worldwide. The ranking is decided based on recommendations by associates and\r\nclients. The survey listed 10 patent firms in Israel, ranking them in three tiers, ranking Ehrlich\r\n&amp; Fenster at pole position in the first tier.\r\n\r\nEhrlich &amp; Partners was established in 2000 by Dr. Gal Ehrlich. Since then, the company has grown\r\nand flourished to encompass well over one hundred staff, of which sixty are professional employees.\r\n\r\nIn 2006, Ehrlich &amp; Partners merged with Fenster &amp; Company, becoming Ehrlich &amp; Fenster. The merger\r\nfurther propelled Ehrlich &amp; Fenster’s ability to provide clients and associates alike the\r\nprofessionalism required to be rated first in the profession.\r\nEhrlich &amp; Fenster specializes in handling patent portfolios\r\nof various size and complexity, from private entrepreneurs to the largest international\r\norganizations. The firm\r\nis known for having unrivaled knowledge in all technological fields, superb expertise in the art\r\nof patent drafting and prosecution, diligent management, and personal service rendered to each and\r\nevery client.\r\n\r\nDespite its meteoric growth and acknowledged success, Ehrlich &amp; Fenster does not rest on its\r\nlaurels, but rather continues to serve the R&amp;D community in Israel in offering yet better and new\r\nservices.\r\n\r\nTwo current areas of expansion are in the field of Trademarks and services rendered to foreign\r\nassociates. Ehrlich &amp; Fenster aggressively pursues effective and broad trademark protection for\r\ntheir clients with the Israel Trade Mark Registry, based on an understanding of the client''s\r\nbusiness needs.\r\n\r\nEhrlich &amp; Fenster Patent Attorneys also file more PCT applications than any other Israeli patent\r\nattorney firm and have a rapidly increasing number of national\r\nphase filings all over the world.', 'Managing IP World Survey 2008 ranks Ehrlich & Fenster as Israel''s No. 1 Patent Attorneys Firm', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'managing-ip-world-survey-2008-ranks-ehrlich-fenster-as-israels-no-1-patent-attorneys-firm', '', '', '2013-10-16 12:16:31', '2013-10-16 12:16:31', '', 0, 'http://ipatent.co.il/?p=700', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(701, 2, '2013-10-16 12:10:11', '2013-10-16 12:10:11', 'The Managing IP World Survey found Ehrlich &amp; Fenster to be Israel’s No. 1 Patent Attorneys firm. The Managing IP ranking is based on extensive research and interviews with patent practitioners worldwide. A team of researchers based in London, Hong Kong and New York contacted firms in 65 jurisdictions to ask them for information  and feedback on the rankings.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe results of the survey highlight the unparallel level of service offered to clients by the Ehrlich &amp; Fenster team. Managing IP surveys concentrate  on quality of services offered to clients and associates worldwide. The ranking is decided based on recommendations by associates and clients. The survey listed 10 patent firms in Israel, ranking them in three tiers, ranking Ehrlich &amp; Fenster at pole position in the first tier.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nEhrlich &amp; Partners was established in 2000 by Dr. Gal Ehrlich. Since then, the company has grown  and flourished to encompass well over one hundred staff, of which sixty are professional employees.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nIn 2006, Ehrlich &amp; Partners merged with Fenster &amp; Company, becoming Ehrlich &amp; Fenster. The merger further propelled Ehrlich &amp; Fenster’s ability to provide clients and associates alike the professionalism required to be rated first in the profession.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nEhrlich &amp; Fenster specializes in handling patent portfolios of various size and complexity, from private entrepreneurs to the largest international organizations. The firm\n\nis known  for having unrivaled  knowledge  in all technological fields, superb expertise in the art of patent drafting and prosecution, diligent management, and personal service rendered  to each and every client.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nDespite its meteoric  growth  and acknowledged success, Ehrlich &amp; Fenster does not rest on its laurels, but rather continues to serve the R&amp;D community in Israel in offering yet better and new services.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nTwo current  areas of expansion are in the field of Trademarks and services rendered to foreign associates. Ehrlich &amp; Fenster aggressively pursues effective and broad trademark protection for their clients with the Israel Trade Mark Registry, based on an understanding of the client''s business needs.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nEhrlich &amp; Fenster Patent Attorneys  also file more PCT applications than any other Israeli patent attorney firm and have a rapidly increasing number  of national phase filings all over the world.', 'Managing IP World Survey 2008 ranks Ehrlich & Fenster as Israel''s No. 1 Patent Attorneys Firm', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '700-revision', '', '', '2013-10-16 12:10:11', '2013-10-16 12:10:11', '', 700, 'http://ipatent.co.il/?p=701', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
