(979, 2, '2013-11-13 07:12:53', '2013-11-13 07:12:53', 'Trade secrets are a common and powerful form of intellectual property, sometimes the most valued asset of the company. Businesses must be particularly careful when dealing with trade secrets because, unlike the case with patents or trademarks, failure to maintain the confidentiality required for trade secret protection can result in a complete loss of rights. Examples of trade secrets include, inter alia, technical information, formulas, germlines, germplasms, reproductive materials, genetic materials, databases, methods, processes, know-how, tolerances, computer programs, source codes, laboratory and research data, designs, improvements, product plans, SOPs and the like.\n\nBusinesses must understand the costs and benefits of different strategies for protecting intellectual property. Some forms of protection, including patent protection and trade secret protection, overlap. Knowing when to protect valuable information as a trade secret and when to protect it through patent procurement is vital to managing and optimizing such assets. Our patent attorneys are experienced in the relative strengths and weaknesses of patent versus trade secret protection that can help determine whether to maintain an invention as a trade secret, seek a patent or maintain a portion thereof as a trade secret, while securing patent protection to the remainder portions.\n\nEhrlich &amp; Fenster works with its clients to establish appropriate procedures to secure their sensitive information. When we encounter an invention or development for which the best IP protection is a trade secret we counsel our clients how to effectively protect the trade secret and to nevertheless generate value for the company.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nEhrlich &amp; Fenster offers a service that includes:\n\n1. Identifying the trade secret;\n\n2. Integrating the secret in the IP portfolio of the client;\n\n3. Documenting the trade secret;\n\n4. Trade secret depository;\n\n5. Creating a reminder system for monitoring updates of the trade secret;\n\n6. When needed, updating the trade secret on a periodic basis;\n\n7. Guiding the client how to protect the secret;\n\n8. Assisting in protecting the secret;\n\n9. Forming a legal situation whereby breach of confidentiality will more likely be enforceable against a third party; and\n\n&nbsp;', 'Trade Secrets', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '545-autosave', '', '', '2013-11-13 07:12:53', '2013-11-13 07:12:53', '', 545, 'http://ipatent.co.il/?p=979', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(980, 1, '2013-09-11 22:57:21', '2013-09-11 22:57:21', 'The firm helps clients identify, determine, and broaden the protection scope of their core Intellectual Property. This is achieved by analyzing and assessing the potential business opportunities that may emerge from the client’s innovative technologies and areas of invention. Ehrlich &amp; Fenster strategic advantage is in its ability to identify the individual or multi-core technologies often hidden within a technological development. The firm pursues all the potential business directions available to a client including buying, in-and-out licensing, selling and international expansion.\r\n\r\nEach department is involved in drafting and prosecuting patent applications, including opposition procedures, in rendering opinions regarding IP matters, IP related Due Diligence processes, and in devising IP and commercialization strategies. There are over a dozen patent attorneys having Ph.D. degrees in all disciplines, with most Department heads having a doctorate degree.\r\n\r\nEhrlich &amp; Fenster provides patent prosecution services in a broad range of technologies to many small and mid-sized companies, as well as to large clients that have critical timing requirements, complex patent applications likely to be embroiled in litigation or interferences, or require specialized technical needs.\r\n<h3>Among our practice areas:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">Biotech, Immunology, Agrotechnology, Bioinformatics, Biochemistry</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">Pharmacology, Chemistry</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">Physics, Mechanics, Medical Devices, Cleantech</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">Electronics, Elecrooptics, Computer Hardware</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;">Computer Software, Telecommunications, Business Methods</span></li>\r\n</ul>', 'Patents', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '523-revision-3', '', '', '2013-09-11 22:57:21', '2013-09-11 22:57:21', '', 523, 'http://ipatent.co.il/?p=980', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
