(990, 1, '2013-10-20 21:31:36', '2013-10-20 21:31:36', 'The Litigation Support department deals with cases which involve actual or potential litigation or which involve due diligence or analysis of patents or patent portfolios during acquisition or investment.\r\n\r\nWe advise clients on preparing for litigation and help clients to find suitable representation overseas. We continue to be involved in the technical and interface aspects of these litigations remaining deeply involved in these cases during their entire lifetime. We have had a major part in cases of this type in the US, the EPO, the UK, Germany, Japan, China and Singapore. We also represent clients in discussions with foreign patent holders who assert their patents against our clients.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Litigation Support', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '541-revision-5', '', '', '2013-10-20 21:31:36', '2013-10-20 21:31:36', '', 541, 'http://ipatent.co.il/?p=990', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(991, 1, '2013-10-30 08:45:04', '2013-10-30 08:45:04', 'Nowadays, industrial design and the aesthetic features of products are becoming increasingly more important to both companies and consumer. A Design protects the overall visual appearance of a product or a part of a product, resulting from its features- contours, colors, shape, texture or materials. Meaning, legal protection is given to the way the product looks. A Registered Design can be a valuable intellectual property right, as it may create the basis of an infringement action.\r\n\r\nOur Design Department, specializes in identifying the needs of each and every client, especially those whose products are seasonal in nature and require expedited processing. Our design department also specializes in preparing and filing Design application in Israel and abroad, as well as in design patents prosecution and enforcement. In filing design applications, as in all other aspects, we ensure achievement of our clients business goals in the procurement of strong IP portfolio and combined strategy.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Design', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '539-revision-5', '', '', '2013-10-30 08:45:04', '2013-10-30 08:45:04', '', 539, 'http://ipatent.co.il/?p=991', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(992, 1, '2013-09-11 13:22:50', '2013-09-11 13:22:50', 'Plant breeders'' rights are rights granted to the breeder of a new variety of plant that give him exclusivity over the propagating material (including seed, cuttings, divisions, tissue culture) and harvested material (cut flowers, fruit, foliage) of a new variety for a number of years.\r\n\r\nSeed is submitted to the official plant variety office to check that it is distinct, stable, and uniform. If these tests are passed, exclusive rights are granted for a period of 20 years (or 25 years, for trees and vines). Annual renewal fees are required to maintain the rights.\r\n\r\nThe Breeders Rights Department handles the submission and processing of such applications in Israel.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Breeder''s Rights', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '543-revision-3', '', '', '2013-09-11 13:22:50', '2013-09-11 13:22:50', '', 543, 'http://ipatent.co.il/?p=992', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
